{"id":455838,"url":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wolf_Koenig","text":"e=\"preserve\">Wolf Koenig (October 17, 1927 \u2013 June 26, 2014) was a German-born Canadian movie director, producer, animator and cinematographer. He was a founder of Direct Cinema at the National Film Board of Canada (NFB). For NFB, he worked on movies such as \"Neighbours\" (1952) and \"Lonely Boy\" (1962). His animations included \"What on Earth!\" (1966) and \"The House That Jack Built\" (1967).\nKoenig was born in Dresden, Saxony. He and his family fled Nazi Germany for Canada in 1937.\nKoenig died on June 26, 2014 in Toronto, Ontario, aged 86.","categories":[],"infobox_types":[],"annotations":[{"uri":"Germans","surface_form":"German","offset":66},{"uri":"Canadians","surface_form":"Canadian","offset":78},{"uri":"Movie_director","surface_form":"movie director","offset":87},{"uri":"Producer","surface_form":"producer","offset":103},{"uri":"Animator","surface_form":"animator","offset":113},{"uri":"Cinematographer","surface_form":"cinematographer","offset":126},{"uri":"Direct_Cinema","surface_form":"Direct Cinema","offset":163},{"uri":"National_Film_Board_of_Canada","surface_form":"National Film Board of Canada","offset":184},{"uri":"Movie","surface_form":"movie","offset":243},{"uri":"Neighbours_(1952_movie)","surface_form":"Neighbours","offset":259},{"uri":"Lonely_Boy_(movie)","surface_form":"Lonely Boy","offset":283},{"uri":"Animation","surface_form":"animation","offset":307},{"uri":"What_on_Earth%21","surface_form":"What on Earth!","offset":328},{"uri":"The_House_That_Jack_Built_(1967_mocvie)","surface_form":"The House That Jack Built","offset":356},{"uri":"Dresden","surface_form":"Dresden","offset":410},{"uri":"Saxony","surface_form":"Saxony","offset":419},{"uri":"Nazi_Germany","surface_form":"Nazi Germany","offset":450},{"uri":"Toronto","surface_form":"Toronto","offset":515},{"uri":"Ontario","surface_form":"Ontario","offset":524}]}